                            <comment id="110226" author="adilger" created="Fri, 20 Mar 2015 17:18:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please also include a test for OI Scrub rebuilding OI files for an MDT in recovery.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="110059" author="yong.fan" created="Thu, 19 Mar 2015 00:47:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently, the initial OI scrub will fix some key files before recovery, such as ROOT, .lustre, and so on. These files either have known FID or not care about what the FID is. As for the update log, it is new for DNE2, we can make the initial OI scrub to handle them before recovery. But because the update log&apos;s FID is stored as its name, then the initial OI scrub needs to handle them specially.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
